data.text: @jm1727g1 Good point, let's have a conversation and break it down together tomorrow.
this needs to be broken down into multiple cards

Rather than making cards I thought it would be better to list it out here to discuss as a group. 

Breakdown into smaller tasks:

1. Display an idea (just the idea, no upvotes, no downvotes, no comments, no files)
2. Display Upvotes and downvotes
3. Display Comments
4. Display Files and allow them to be downloaded
5. limit amount of comments being shown on an idea to 2 or 3, add option to click a button to see more comments
6. Allow users to upvote and downvote ideas
7. Allow comments to be added
8. Loop through database and show multiple ideas, limited to 5 until show more button is clicked.

the Idea is to tackle each bit of functionality a step at a time, we could have one person working on getting the document system working while someone else works on getting the comments displayed and someone else is putting together the front end for this.

listing.name: Agile Tools
listing.description:
Agile Tools by Corrello allows you to add story points and WIP Limits to Trello. It is fully integrated with [Corrello Agile Dashboards](https://getcorrello.com?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=directory&utm_campaign=agile_tools_powerup) **[burndowns](https://getcorrello.com/Burndown?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=directory&utm_campaign=agile_tools_powerup_burndown)**, **[CFDs](https://getcorrello.com/cumulative-flow-diagram?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=directory&utm_campaign=agile_tools_powerup_cfd)**, **burnups**, and **[cycle time](https://getcorrello.com/cycle-time?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=directory&utm_campaign=agile_tools_powerup_cycletime)** charts. 

Agile Tools is completely free and is the perfect Power-Up for Scrum or Kanban teams using Trello (or even teams blending a mix of Scrum and Kanban :) )

![Features GIF](https://getcorrello.com/manifests/agiletools/images/agiletools.gif)

**Features:**

 - Story points on Cards
 - One click migration of story points from Scrum for Trello
 - WIP limits
-  Count of Cards in each List

listing.name: Time Tracking & Reporting
listing.description:
##  The easiest way for your team to log time directly in Trello##

Help your team log time on Trello cards to track work. Create and export reports to see aggregated data.

This Power-Up was built ground up for Trello and is not an integration. Everything you need is inside your Trello board.

![Time Tracking & Reporting for Trello](https://d1jf30w5bnlnbf.cloudfront.net/listings/time-tracking/tt-demo.gif?utm_source=powerup_listing)

To get started

- Open a card, pick a date, a team member and log the number of hours spent. If you forget to log time, you can pick a date back in time or do it all at once at the end of the week. It works either way.
- Create reports grouped by cards or team members within a date range to get a detailed view on the projects progress. Youll see where hours have been spent, whos worked on what, and which tasks have accumulated the most time. 
- Export reports into Excel or CSV for your records.

![Time Tracking & Reporting - Excel](https://time-tracking-trello.s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/tt-excel.png)

This Power-Up is a time tracker tool for logging work and viewing reports. Useful for billing and invoicing clients, keeping up with accounting, resource planning, seeing how much time has been spent on projects, as a time sheeting system, and more. Export formats include Excel (XLSX) and CSV.

---

Pricing: $10/month for one board with unlimited members (or $100/year to get two months free)
_We dont charge per team member  you only pay for the boards you purchase a license for._

By enabling Time Tracking & Reporting on your Trello boards, you accept our [Terms and Conditions](https://orahapps.com/terms).

Get in touch with questions or feedback at support@orahapps.com
